To enact section 959.22 of the Revised Code to 1
prohibit a person from declawing a cat. 2
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 959.22 of the Revised Code be 3
enacted to read as follows: 4
Sec. 959.22. (A) As used in this section : 5
(1) "Licensed veterinarian" has the same meaning as in 6
section 4741.01 of the Revised Code. 7
(2) "Onychectomy" means a procedure in which a portion of 8
the paw of a cat is amputated or the claw of a cat is disabled, 9
including a procedure that is commonly referred to as declawing. 10
(3) "Partial digital amputation" means a procedure for the 11
excision of some or all of one or more of the phalanges of the 12
paw of a cat. 13
(4) "Phalangectomy" means a procedure for the excision of 14
one or more of the phalanges of the paw of a cat. 15
(5) "Tendonectomy" means a procedure in which the tendons 16
to the limbs, paws, or toes of a cat are cut or modified so that 17
the cat's claws cannot function normally. 18

