(6) "Therapeutic purpose" means a purpose necessary to 19
address a physical medical condition of a cat, such as an 20
existing or recurring physical illness, infection, disease, 21
injury, or abnormal condition in a claw that compromises the 22
cat's health. "Therapeutic purpose" does not mean cosmetic or 23
aesthetic purposes or purposes of convenience in the keeping, 24
harboring, or handling of a cat. 25
(B)(1) No person, by any means, shall knowingly perform an 26
onychectomy, a partial digit amputation, a phalangectomy, a 27
tendonectomy, or any other procedure to alter a cat's toes, 28
claws, or paws to prevent the normal functioning of the cat's 29
toes, claws, or paws. 30
(2) Division (B)(1) does not apply to either of the 31
following: 32
(a) A procedure that is determined to be necessary for a 33
therapeutic purpose by a licensed veterinarian; 34
(b) A procedure that solely involves the trimming of a 35
nonviable claw husk or placing a nonpermanent nail cap on a cat. 36
(C) If a licensed veterinarian determines that a procedure 37
is necessary for a therapeutic purpose under division (B)(2)(a) 38
of this section, the licensed veterinarian, within ten business 39
days after performing the procedure, shall file a written 40
statement with the state veterinary medical licensing board that 41
includes all of the following: 42
(1) The purpose of the procedure, including a laboratory 43
pathology report confirming the pathology; 44
(2) Identifying information of the cat, including its 45
microchip number, if applicable, age, gender, markings, and a 46
photo of the cat's face; 47

