(3) Identifying information of the cat's owner or keeper, 48
including the owner's current address and telephone number. 49
The licensed veterinarian shall provide a copy of the 50
written statement to the owner or keeper of the cat. 51
(D) The director of agriculture shall impose a civil 52
penalty against a person who violates division (B)(1) of this 53
section in an amount as follows: 54
(1) One thousand dollars on a first offense; 55
(2) One thousand five hundred dollars on a second offense; 56
(3) Two thousand five hundred dollars on a third and any 57
subsequent offense. 58
The director shall afford the person an opportunity for an 59
adjudication hearing under Chapter 119. of the Revised Code to 60
challenge the director's determination that the person committed 61
such violation. 62

